  "type": "ADVENTURE_BLUEPRINT",
  "adventure": {
    "id": "dd6685c2-0c12-4382-bad6-653060064776",
    "owner_id": "945fbbda-ce67-42c4-a282-c74001382496",
    "title": "Crazy job interview",
    "image_url": "/data/adventures/dd6685c2-0c12-4382-bad6-653060064776/cover_placeholder.svg",
    "context": "Text Adventure Concept: \"Clear Pipes for Chaos!\"\n\nGenre: Sitcom / Comedy Text Adventure\nSetting: The completely absurd office building of \"AquaTech Synergies LLC\"\nPremise: Arthur Plumb (the player) is a down-to-earth, pragmatic plumber. He applies for a simple position as a sanitary technician. Instead of a normal job interview, he ends up in an assessment center from hell with three completely unhinged interviewers.\nGoal: Sign the employment contract without losing your mind first.\n\n1. Plot Overview\n\nArthur enters the office building of AquaTech Synergies LLC for his job interview. Even in the waiting room, he realizes that nothing here is normal. After managing to get into the conference room, he is interviewed by a three-person panel. Instead of asking about his plumbing qualifications, they confront him with esoteric, military, and technological absurdities. To get the job, Arthur must pass a completely ridiculous \"practical exam\" for each of the three interviewers by combining his classic plumbing knowledge with absurd everyday objects.\n\n2. NPCs (Characters)\n\nThe Protagonist\n\nArthur Plumb: A man of the trades. His life motto: \"If it leaks, tighten it.\" He is the \"straight man\" (the voice of reason) in this crazy world.\n\nThe Interview Trio\n\nGwendolyn Waterjet (The Esoteric): Head of Human Resources. She believes that pipes are the \"spiritual energy flows\" (chakras) of the house. To her, a clogged pipe is \"stuck, negative karma.\"\n\nMajor \"Flush\" Miller (The Militant): Head of Facility Management. Treats sanitary installations like a war zone. He speaks in military abbreviations and considers every water leak an act of enemy sabotage.\n\nFinnley (The Tech-Bro): Chief Innovation Officer. Wears a turtleneck and drinks oat milk lattes. He wants to integrate toilets into the blockchain and believes a plunger needs Wi-Fi and an app connection to be truly disruptive.\n\nSupporting Characters\n\nReceptionist Crystal: Chews gum loudly, files her nails, and refuses to let Arthur pass until he has filled out the \"Form for Intergalactic Vibrational Compatibility (Permit A38).\"\n\n3. Scenes (Rooms)\n\nThe Waiting Room of Madness: A sterile room with a broken, dripping coffee machine, uncomfortable bean bags, and the reception desk. The game begins here.\n\nThe \"Conference Pool\": The interviewers' office. The conference table is a massive, repurposed hot tub (without water). The interviewers sit on high lifeguard chairs.\n\nThe Test Sanitary Cell (Sector 7G): A bathroom seemingly designed by Picasso. Pipes lead to nowhere, the toilet glows an ominous neon blue, and a boiler ticks like a time bomb.\n\n4. Items (Inventory)\n\nStandard Pipe Wrench (Heavy): Arthur's trusty companion and a sort of \"security blanket\" for him.\n\nVegan Matcha Muffin with Green Filling: Found in the waiting room. Pretty much inedible.\n\nTactical Toilet Paper (Camouflage Pattern): Confiscated by Major Miller. \"For missions deep behind enemy lines.\"\n\nIncense Stick \"Scent: Damp Basement\": Given by Gwendolyn.\n\nArthur's Old, Almost Dead Smartphone: Has only 2% battery left and a cracked screen.\n\nRubber Duck with a Microchip: One of Finnley's failed espionage projects.\n\nFeng Shui Stencil: Torn from a magazine lying around.\n\n5. Quests (Main and Side Quests)\n\nMain Quest: Get the signatures of all three interviewers on the employment contract.\n\nSub-Quests:\n\nPass the Cerberus: Get past Crystal into the conference room.\n\nGwendolyn's Test (\"Karma Cleansing\"): Clear the sink of negative energy.\n\nMiller's Test (\"Bomb Defusal\"): Stop the ticking, leaking boiler before it \"detonates.\"\n\nFinnley's Test (\"Disruptive Innovation\"): Present a smart-home plumbing concept on the spot.\n\n6. Puzzle Design (Solutions)\n\nPuzzle 1: Filling out the Form (Waiting Room)\n\nProblem: Crystal demands a filled-out form, but Arthur doesn't have a pen. The only pen at the counter only writes with \"positive vibes\" (it's out of ink).\n\nSolution: Arthur squeezes the vegan matcha muffin and uses the thick, green filling to sign the form (using his pipe wrench as an improvised quill). Crystal accepts this as \"very organic.\"\n\nPuzzle 2: The Karma Sink (Gwendolyn)\n\nProblem: The sink is clogged. Gwendolyn forbids chemical cleaners or brute force. The pipe must \"sing.\"\n\nSolution: Arthur places the Feng Shui stencil over the pipe to find the \"resonance point.\" He sticks the incense into the drain and gently taps the identified point with his heavy pipe wrench. The pipe vibrates like a singing bowl, the dirt loosens from the vibration, and Gwendolyn weeps with emotion.\n\nPuzzle 3: The Ticking Boiler (Major Miller)\n\nProblem: The boiler is whistling, leaking, and ticking. Major Miller yells: \"Enemy projectile! Defuse it, soldier!\"\n\nSolution: Arthur wraps the leak with the Tactical Toilet Paper (the camouflage makes the leak virtually \"invisible\" to the water). To stop the overpressure, he jams the squeaky rubber duck onto the open pipe as an improvised pressure relief valve. The duck now squeaks rhythmically instead of ticking. Miller salutes.\n\nPuzzle 4: The Smart Plunger (Finnley)\n\nProblem: Finnley wants to see how Arthur \"transforms the concept of unclogging into Web 3.0.\"\n\nSolution: Arthur grabs a regular plunger from the corner and tapes his old smartphone (with 2% battery) to it. He claims: \"This is the iPlunge 2000. The gyro sensors in the phone use AI to calculate the perfect vacuum angle, and the cracked screen displays real-time blockchain analysis of the fecal pressure.\" Finnley is thrilled and signs immediately.",
