      "protagonist": {
        "name": "Arthur Plumb",
        "role": "Plumber",
        "description": "Arthur Plumb is a rugged yet unflappable tradesman in his mid-40s, wearing faded overalls with countless patch repairs. His calloused hands and oil-stained tool belt speak of decades spent tightening leaky faucets and untangling bureaucratic nonsense. In this surreal corporate parody, he's the only sane man left standing \u2014 still armed with realism and a pipe wrench against cosmic nonsense.",
